g 'N/A'\");\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:3:description: Review automated pull requests with the `library-bulk-update` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that bumps tested versions for existing libraries, including approve vs close decisions, CI checks, diff-scope validation, and verification of `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` changes.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:15:- Close the PR when it contains unrelated changes such as workflow files, Gradle files, generated sources, or test code that clearly did not belong in a bulk version update.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:24:   - Read the body and verify it is a bot-generated \"Added tested versions\" summary.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:64:   - Review `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` with the same rules used by `PopulateArtifactURLs`.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:65:   - For pre-release promotions, verify the `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` values were rendered from the old version to the promoted `metadata-version` or otherwise corrected to an exact-version URL. Do not accept stale URLs that still point at the old pre-release.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:77:- `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` must point to the exact library version in the changed entry.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/ReadmeBadgeSummarySupport.java:892:            return \"N/A\";\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:1925:            reason=\"test_generation_failed\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2006:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2023:    if candidate.reason == \"test_generation_failed\" or candidate.coverage is None:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2031:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2033:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2179:        \"Inspect the available logs, generated tests, Gradle output, and metrics. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2312:    if candidate.reason in {\"test_generation_failed\", \"job_failed\"}:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4802:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect runtime-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, dependency adjustments, runtime configuration, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/DiscoveredArtifactMetadata.java:22:        @JsonProperty(\"documentation-url\")\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:42:   - Be suspicious of changes to build logic, workflows, unrelated libraries, generated sources outside the target test directory, or wide refactors.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/CheckDocLinksTask.java:35: * <p>Walks the repository for {@code .md} files (excluding generated/build/test\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/TestedVersionUpdaterTask.java:229:                promoteUrl(\"documentation-url\", entry.documentationUrl(), oldVersion, newVersion, UrlVerification.RESOLVES)\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/TestedVersionUpdaterTask.java:234:        if (!hasText(currentUrl) || \"N/A\".equals(currentUrl)) {\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:74:Use the `scaffold` task to generate metadata and test stubs:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:111:* `documentation-url`: URL to the project documentation for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:143:     \"documentation-url\": \"https://github.com/example/repo/tree/main/README.md\",\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:155:To populate `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `description` fields in matching `index.json` entries:\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:33:        @JsonProperty(\"documentation-url\")\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:163:The schema follows semver, and **minor- and patch-version bumps** (e.g., `v2.0.1` → `v2.0.2` or `v2.0.x` → `v2.1.0`) are guaranteed to be backward-compatible with native-build-tools. Minor bumps add new optional fields used by the website, the test harness, or future tooling (`requires`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, `repository-url`); patch bumps refine validation of those same auxiliary fields. The plugin reads only the six fields enumerated above, so an older native-build-tools release continues to resolve metadata correctly against any newer minor or patch version of the schema. Only a **major-version bump** can break the contract, which NFR-4 forbids — schema changes are additive only.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:2:When the repository doesn’t have reachability metadata for a library you are using, the easiest way to generate it is to execute the test suite of the library with the Native Image Agent enabled. The agent is installed together with native-image and can be used to identify elements used during application execution that cannot be discovered by static analysis.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:26:To run the test task with the agent, run `./gradlew -Pagent` test. This will generate metadata in the build output directory of the project (under `build/native/agent/test`).\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:59:Conditional metadata can be generated by inserting the Native Image Agent options into the command line of the JVM that runs the tests.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:296:    task.setDescription(\"Uses a coding agent command to fill source-code-url, repository-url, test-code-url, documentation-url, description, and language in matching metadata index entries.\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:300:tasks.register(\"discoverArtifactMetadata\", DiscoverArtifactMetadata.class) { task ->\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:843:// gradle generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix -PbaseCommit=<base> -PnewCommit=<head> -PspringAotBranch=<branch> -PspringAotPath=/path/to/spring-aot-smoke-tests\n./docs/CI.md:25:  - Uses: generateMatrixBatchedCoordinates to build a matrix (java + os). Runs full tests, pulls only allowed Docker images, then disables Docker networking for deterministic runs.\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: [`generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to compute only newly added [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) from the base/head diff and pairs them with the matching [`metadata-version`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json), then runs [`run-consecutive-tests.sh`](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh) only for those added versions.\n./docs/CI.md:34:  - Uses: generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix. Pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, then runs tests.\n./docs/CI.md:37:  - Uses: generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix to compute impacted Spring AOT projects and produce a matrix; runs triaged native tests via [.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh).\n./docs/CI.md:43:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/CI.md:49:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect compile-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, imports, renamed APIs, dependency adjustments, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:157:    if line_coverage != \"N/A\":\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:161:    if instruction_coverage == \"N/A\":\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:350:    generated_loc = count_generated_loc(tests_root)\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:89:- Iteratively generate a meaningful, cohesive JUnit test suite for library using AI.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/utility_scripts/gradle_test_runner.py:136:The command was stopped as a suspected test deadlock or leaked-thread hang. Fix the generated tests so every test\n./forge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:26:    \"documentation\": \"documentation-url\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:80: