ta with weak tests should be treated as failures that need investigation.\\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:123:- the generated test logic is valid and meaningful\\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:137:- generated tests are trivial, broken, or misleading\\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:158:- describe the important observations from logs, generated tests, and metrics\\n./metadata/javax.validation/validation-api/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/validation/validation-api/$version$/validation-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/javax.validation/validation-api/index.json:23:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/validation/validation-api/$version$/validation-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/javax.validation/validation-api/index.json:37:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/validation/validation-api/$version$/validation-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:54:   `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` as required.\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:240:    Keep -- yes --> KeepOK([Phase returns ok=true,<br/>keep generated tests])\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:262:    GenMD[generateMetadata] --> Test{./gradlew test passes?}\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:303:| Reachability-repo Gradle tasks | `scaffold`, `populateArtifactURLs`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `test`, `nativeTest`, `generateMetadata`, `generateLibraryStats`. |\\n./forge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:62:          \\\"const\\\": \\\"N/A\\\"\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:139:                    \\\"Dynamic access report generation failed for {} with exit code {}. Writing dynamicAccess as N/A.\\\",\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/