   Java<SUP><FONT SIZE=-2>TM</FONT></SUP> Management Extensions\n    (JMX<SUP><FONT SIZE=-2>TM</FONT></SUP>)</H1>\n  <H2>\n    Reference Implementation Version 1.2.1</B></BR>\n  </H2>\n</CENTER>\n\n\n<!-- ============================================================= -->\n<BLOCKQUOTE>\n\nThe Java <SUP><FONT SIZE=-2>TM</FONT></SUP> Management extensions \n(JMX<SUP><FONT SIZE=-2>TM</FONT></SUP>) provide a standard for instrumenting \nmanageable resources and developing dynamic agents. This release contains the \nJMX reference implementation (RI) for the instrumentation and agent levels of \nthe specification.<P> \n\nThe Java classes which make up the RI are supported on\nthe Java 2 Platform, Standard Edition (J2SE), version 1.4:\n\n<A HREF=\"http://java.sun.com/webapps/getjava/BrowserRedirect?locale=en\">\n<IMG SRC=\"doc/images/get_java_red_button.gif\" ALT = \"Java: Get It Now!\" ALIGN=CENTER>\n</A>\n<P>\n\nAs a result of the \n<A HREF=\"http://jcp.org/en/home/index\">Java Community Process</A>, \nJMX is an extension to the Java programming\nlanguage, and its packages use the <code>javax</code> prefix. The RI\nalso includes some internal classes in the\n<code>com.sun.jmx.*</code> packages.<P>\n\nIn this software bundle, Sun also provides classes for an\nHTML adaptor: these are independent of the JMX specification and are\nprovided only for demonstration purposes. These classes are in the\n<code>com.sun.jdmk.*</code> packages.\n\n</BLOCKQUOTE>\n\n\n<!-- ============================================================= -->\n<BLOCKQUOTE>\n  <B><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF=\"doc/files.html\">File List</A>\n  </FONT></B><BR>\n\nIncludes the list of all components in this bundle and how to use them.\n\n</BLOCKQUOTE>\n\n\n<!-- ============================================================= -->\n<BLOCKQUOTE>\n  <B><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF=\"RELEASE_NOTES.txt\">Release Notes</A>\n  </FONT></B><BR>\n\nThe Release Notes cover the features and known limitations of this release.\n\n</BLOCKQUOTE>\n\n\n<!-- ============================================================= -->\n<BLOCKQUOTE>\n\nexec\n/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n '1_2|\\\\\"'$version'\"\\\\\"'$'\"' metadata/javax metadata/com.sun metadata/org.mortbay.jetty metadata/javax.servlet metadata/javax.el metadata/javax.portlet | head -120\" in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/3039-b4b48c9b\n succeeded in 0ms:\nrg: metadata/javax: No such file or directory (os error 2)\nrg: metadata/com.sun: No such file or directory (os error 2)\nmetadata/javax.portlet/portlet-api/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/portlet/portlet-api/$version$/portlet-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.portlet/portlet-api/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/portlet/portlet-api/$version$/portlet-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.el/javax.el-api/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/el/javax.el-api/$version$/javax.el-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.el/javax.el-api/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/el/javax.el-api/$version$/javax.el-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.el/el-api/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/el/el-api/$version$/el-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/index.json:19:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/javax/servlet/servlet-api/$version$/servlet-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/index.json:22:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://download.oracle.com/otn-pub/jcp/servlet-$version$-fr-spec-oth-JSpec/servlet-2_4-fr-spec.pdf\",\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/index.json:33:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/javax/servlet/servlet-api/$version$/servlet-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/ja